    (pointer-sized opaque value) to its empty-queue state. Per Microsoft
    documentation
    (https://learn.microsoft.com/windows/win32/api/synchapi/nf-synchapi-initializeconditionvariable)
    pairs with SleepConditionVariableSRW / WakeConditionVariable /
    WakeAllConditionVariable. Used by Runa's condvar_create.
    @End Reasoning

    @Implementation
    Single Win32 call; PCONDITION_VARIABLE in X0; void return.
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Sub-100ns; effectively a single store of zero to the cv word.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    No privileges required.
    @End Security_Scope

    Let result be 0
    Inline Assembly:
        ldr x0, [sp, #-8]

        bl InitializeConditionVariable

        mov x0, #0
        str x0, [sp, #-16]
    End Assembly
    Return result
End Process

Process called "windows_arm64_api_sleep_condition_variable_srw" takes cv_ptr as Integer, lock_ptr as Integer, ms_timeout as Integer, flags as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    SleepConditionVariableSRW - atomically release the supplied SRWLOCK
    and block on the CONDITION_VARIABLE until woken or the timeout
