    Four-argument Win32 call. Microsoft ARM64 ABI: X0 = cv, X1 = lock,
    X2 = ms, X3 = flags. Returns BOOL in X0 (0 = timeout, nonzero =
    signal).
    @End Implementation

    @Performance_Hints
    Uncontended signal path: 2 syscalls (release + wait, then reacquire).
    Contended timeout: 1 syscall with timer setup.
    @End Performance_Hints

    @Security_Scope
    Caller must hold the supplied SRWLOCK in the mode that matches flags.
    @End Security_Scope

