Note:
============================================================================
ERROR HANDLING HELPERS
============================================================================
:End Note

Process called "windows_arm64_is_error" takes result as Integer returns Integer:
    Note:
    Check if result indicates an error
    result: result from Windows API call
    Returns: 1 if error, 0 if success
    :End Note
    
    If result is equal to 0 or result is equal to windows_arm64_INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE:
        Return 1
    End If
    
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "windows_arm64_get_error_message" takes error_code as Integer returns String:
    Note:
    Get error message for error code
    error_code: Windows error code
    Returns: error message string
    :End Note
    
    If error_code is equal to windows_arm64_ERROR_SUCCESS:
        Return "Success"
    Otherwise If error_code is equal to windows_arm64_ERROR_FILE_NOT_FOUND:
        Return "File not found"
    Otherwise If error_code is equal to windows_arm64_ERROR_ACCESS_DENIED:
        Return "Access denied"
    Otherwise If error_code is equal to windows_arm64_ERROR_INVALID_HANDLE:
        Return "Invalid handle"
    Otherwise If error_code is equal to windows_arm64_ERROR_NOT_ENOUGH_MEMORY:
        Return "Not enough memory"
    Otherwise If error_code is equal to windows_arm64_ERROR_INVALID_PARAMETER:
        Return "Invalid parameter"
    End If
    
    Return "Unknown error"
End Process